      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW INFLAME (2) impressive display when ran right away after leading to make it two on end at Warrnambool over 390m (22.28). Consistent performer from this draw with a win and three minor placings to his credit. Well placed and can measure up. GLISTENING (1) pinged the lids and was in the firing line throughout but drifted out of it when 6th at Horsham in a Grade 5. Has ability and is one of the better chances. BULL DURHAM (7) comes off an average run last start when sixth at Warragul over 400m behind Faye Valentine (23.17) in a Grade 4. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from four starts. Can measure up this time. VACATION CALLING (3) was in the money again last time and not beaten far when second (22.83) at Geelong in a Grade 5.",
